        "parents": [
          {
            "commit": "f5e8090ae871c6075c29bb378da1204ef9c7beeb",
            "subject": "LU-2940 llite: Fix for oops in vvp_pgcache_show()"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Vitaly Fertman",
          "email": "vitaly_fertman@xyratex.com",
          "date": "2013-06-06 19:40:32.000000000",
          "tz": 240
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Oleg Drokin",
          "email": "oleg.drokin@intel.com",
          "date": "2013-08-10 04:12:37.000000000",
          "tz": 0
        },
        "subject": "LU-3433 clio: wrong cl_lock usage",
        "message": "LU-3433 clio: wrong cl_lock usage\n\ngranted lock is moved to HELD state in cl_wait_try() only which is\ndone after upcall for non-agl locks. as the result, lock unuse moves\ncl_lock not to CACHED state, but to NEW state. A parallel thread\ngets this lock and tries to enqueue it - instead of re-using a\ncached lock, cl_enqueue_try() initiates a new enqueue and gets to\nosc_lock_enqueue() where it asserts:\n\nLASSERTF(ols->ols_state == OLS_NEW, ...);\n\nthe state of osc lock is RELEASED already - moved here by unuse.\n\nSigned-off-by: Vitaly Fertman <vitaly_fertman@xyratex.com>\nChange-Id: I611a6e8778871da184db13434d223036625443c8\nReviewed-on: http://review.whamcloud.com/6709\nTested-by: Hudson\nTested-by: Maloo <whamcloud.maloo@gmail.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <oleg.drokin@intel.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
